## Observation 1 — /health 200, server boots clean
{"status":"healthy","database":{"connected":true,"database_type":"PostgreSQL","active_connections":0,"idle_connections":4},"version":"2.3.2","schema_hash":"316c9100f7a872c8c411033ac2a00066"}
## Observation 2 — storage routes 404 across the board even though
## [storage.docs_test] is the canonical-shape config block

GET /storage/v1/list/docs_test → HTTP 404
PUT /storage/v1/object/docs_test/test.txt → HTTP 404

## Container log grep -iE 'storage|with_storage' (post-boot):
  - no 'Storage API mounted at /storage/v1/' line
  - no 'Storage initialized' line
  - no warning about ignored [storage] section either

## Root cause (read at frozen SHA, no edits made):
 1. The binary's main.rs L25-L33 deserializes ServerConfig
    (server_config/mod.rs:L41) — a flat-key struct without a
    'storage' field.
 2. The HashMap-shaped storage config lives on RuntimeConfig
    (config/mod.rs:L60-L120 — fields: server, database, storage,
    files, auth, observers...) which the binary never instantiates.
 3. Server::with_storage(backend) is the only way to wire the
    backend, per builder.rs:L583-L588. The binary never calls it.
 4. Therefore both /storage/v1/* (server/routes/storage/mod.rs)
    and fraiseql_storage::storage_router are unreachable in the
    off-the-shelf binary.

## Implication for the docs page:
 - Posture A (binary-as-shipped): the page must document that
   storage requires a host binary or library use, and document the
   library API (with_storage + create_backend + StorageRouteState
   or fraiseql_storage::StorageState). Same shape as Cycle 1's
   library-API pivot for multi-tenancy.
 - Posture B (feature-request): file a framework issue against
   ~/code/fraiseql asking that the binary's ServerConfig either
   embeds [storage.<name>] / [files.<name>] fields and auto-wires
   them, or that the binary deserialize RuntimeConfig instead.
   GREEN Writer recommends (A) per the Cycle 1 precedent, with a
   '## Known issues' block pointing at the new issue.
